      • is

        public static boolean is(BigDecimal num1,
                         Comparator cmp,
                         BigDecimal num2)
        Evaluates num1 to num2 according to the operand cmp
        For example:
        • is(5, Comparator.LTE, 5) = true
        • is(4, Comparator.LTE, 5) = true
        • is(5, Comparator.LTE, 4) = false
        • is(null, Comparator.EQ, null) = true
        • is(null, Comparator.LTE, null) = false
        Parameters:
        num1 - first number
        cmp - of type Comparator
        num2 - second number
        Returns:
        true if num1 satisfies the operand cmp when evaluated to num2
        false if either of the following is true:
        • Both num1 and num2 are null and Comparator.EQ is not used
        • Both num1 and num2 are null and Comparator.NEQ is used
        • Both num1 and num2 are not null and Comparator.NEQ is used
        • Either one of num1 or num2 is null
        • num1 does not satisfy the operand cmp when evaluated to num2
